Jeanette Chabalala, News24(Picture: Hawks) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; A Hawks officer was shot dead, allegedly by his own colleagues, a spokesperson for the crime-fighting unit said on Monday. Warrant Officer Colbern Mashego pulled over two police officers in Boksburg who were driving to OR Tambo International Airport, allegedly with a bag full of drugs on Sunday evening, Hawks spokesperson Brigadier Hangwani Mulaudzi said.When Mashego approached the car, a shootout broke out. He was shot dead. One of the two officers apparently committed suicide, Mulaudzi said.The second officer, a sergeant, fled the scene and was arrested later. A bag containing drugs was seized.Independent Police Investigative Directorate spokesperson Moses Dlamini said the police officers were driving a Ford Ranger. The shooting happened in Jet Park, near Emperor&rsquo;s Palace casino.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.